<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1522505-does-the-book-ne-ed-to-be-read-in-the">Does the book ne?ed to be read in the series consecutively</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1522505'><a id="like_count_community_question_1522505" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1522505?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">1 like</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F31360.Children_of_the_Mind">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1522505-does-the-book-ne-ed-to-be-read-in-the">2 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1522505-does-the-book-ne-ed-to-be-read-in-the">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/52966326-jack-vasen"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1456179595i/52966326._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/52966326-jack-vasen">Jack Vasen</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Absolutely, but Ender in Exile is a wild card. <br/>I call the middle three (Speaker, Exoncide, Children) the Lusitania trilogy and it&apos;s hard to make sense<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Absolutely, but Ender in Exile is a wild card. <br />I call the middle three (Speaker, Exoncide, Children) the Lusitania trilogy and it's hard to make sense of them without reading in order. It wouldn't be too hard to read these three without Ender's Game, but I consider EG to be the gem of all the Enderverse.<br />Ender in Exile takes place after EG and before these three. It is really the 2nd book written 20 years or so later. It could easily be read with EG leaving these three out.<br />These three books are completely different than EG and somewhat different than Exile. These three spend a lot of time on what I call philosophizing. A lot.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

