  <span id="freeText4879039285896651328" style="display:none">A solid conclusion to the Ender Quartet. <br /><br />It was thoughtfully written and obviously much more than just a science fiction book.<br /><br />A few of my favorite quotes:<br /><br />"But we <i>were</i> there, and during the time we lived, we were alive. That's the truth—what is, what was, what will be—not what could be, what should have been, what never can be. If we die, then our death has meaning to the rest of the universe. Even if our lives are unknown, the fact that someone lived here, and died, that will have repercussions that will shape the universe."<br /><br />"Miro, I'm so sorry. I always felt such pity for you humans because you could only think of one thing at a time and your memories were so imperfect and... now I realize that just getting through the day without killing someone can be an achievement."<br /><br />"Changing the world is good for those who want their names in books. But being happy, that is for those who write their names in the lives of others, and hold the hearts of others as treasure most dear. </span>
